WEBVTT

00:01.210 --> 00:02.960
- Jane, please.
Let me--

00:03.160 --> 00:04.230
Aah!

00:04.430 --> 00:05.490
[screaming]

00:05.690 --> 00:07.660
- It's the cops!
We gotta go!

00:07.860 --> 00:10.710
<i>- If you would just</i>
<i>pick a side, pick a boy,</i>

00:10.910 --> 00:12.100
none of this
would have happened.

00:12.300 --> 00:13.840
- The longer this goes on,
the less likely it is

00:14.040 --> 00:15.450
the Pink Ladies
will get back together.

00:15.650 --> 00:17.980
- Maybe I'm done
being a Pink Lady.

00:18.180 --> 00:21.290
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

00:21.490 --> 00:23.110
<i>- What happened? </i>
<i> - I don't wanna talk about it.</i>

00:23.310 --> 00:24.940
<i>- I always thought</i>
<i>I would have</i>

00:25.140 --> 00:27.600
<i>to change the way I am</i>
<i>for a boy to like me.</i>

00:27.800 --> 00:28.900
- How is it
that you're always so right?

00:29.100 --> 00:30.770
I think I just know you.

00:30.970 --> 00:32.040
You really do.

00:32.240 --> 00:33.780
- So you're with Wally now?
- Yeah.

00:33.980 --> 00:35.210
Wally's a great guy.

00:35.410 --> 00:37.390
He's the greatest.

00:37.590 --> 00:38.910
- Maybe I should
stop worrying so much

00:39.110 --> 00:42.310
<i>about why I feel something</i>
<i>and just feel it.</i>

00:42.510 --> 00:43.660
We can figure this out.

00:43.860 --> 00:44.660
I don't need your help.

00:44.860 --> 00:46.490
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:46.680 --> 00:48.050
<i>- They're both in there</i>
<i>getting expelled.</i>

00:48.250 --> 00:49.880
<i>- So where am I headed next?</i>
<i>- My alma mater.</i>

00:50.080 --> 00:51.620
That's in Connecticut.

00:51.820 --> 00:54.320
I demand an assistant.

00:54.520 --> 00:56.320
- We could get married.
- My parents

00:56.520 --> 00:58.240
- would never go for it.
- I'll talk to them.

00:58.440 --> 00:59.800
<i>- You can't be married</i>
<i>and go to high school.</i>

01:00.000 --> 01:01.330
- What is he doing here?
<i>- Where's Richie?</i>

01:01.530 --> 01:03.020
There's no way he's for this.

01:03.220 --> 01:04.720
- My parents put him on a bus
this afternoon.

01:04.920 --> 01:05.720
<i>He's gone, Jane.</i>

01:05.920 --> 01:08.070
You're Jane Facciano.

01:08.270 --> 01:09.900
Jane Facciano never gives up.

01:10.100 --> 01:12.980
<i>♪ </i>

01:15.720 --> 01:18.950
<i>[soft emotional music]</i>

01:19.150 --> 01:21.560
<i>♪ </i>

01:21.760 --> 01:24.740
<i>- Dearly beloved,</i>
<i>we are gathered here today</i>

01:24.940 --> 01:27.130
<i>to join this man</i>
<i>and this woman</i>

01:27.330 --> 01:28.140
<i>in holy matrimony.</i>

01:28.340 --> 01:30.490
<i>Olivia, you look...</i>

01:30.690 --> 01:31.570
Terrible.

01:31.770 --> 01:34.190
<i>[quirky music]</i>

01:34.380 --> 01:36.270
Yeah, this doesn't work at all.

01:36.470 --> 01:37.800
- What? Nancy!
- Uh-uh.

01:38.000 --> 01:40.630
Oh, that's better.

01:40.830 --> 01:42.850
What are you doing here?

01:43.050 --> 01:44.280
[sighs]

01:44.480 --> 01:47.850
- [speaking Spanish]
- Too late.

01:48.050 --> 01:49.580
She's already
making us quesadillas.

01:51.540 --> 01:53.200
You need to leave. Now.

01:53.400 --> 01:55.160
- We came to tell you
something important.

01:55.360 --> 01:57.730
- [sighs]
I'm not in a listening mood.

01:57.930 --> 02:00.650
<i>[upbeat percussive music]</i>

02:00.850 --> 02:03.950
<i>♪ </i>

02:04.150 --> 02:05.130
<i>[bell dings]</i>

02:05.330 --> 02:10.530
<i>♪ </i>

