<i>♪ So lose that guy </i>

03:46.390 --> 03:47.930
<i>♪ Please, please, please </i>

03:48.130 --> 03:50.190
<i> ♪ Please, please don't do it </i>

03:50.390 --> 03:54.110
<i>♪ Royalty</i>
<i>shouldn't be stoopin' ♪</i>

03:54.310 --> 03:57.590
<i>♪ You're pie in the sky,</i>
<i>the apple of eyes ♪</i>

03:57.790 --> 03:59.460
<i>♪ He's not worth your time </i>

03:59.660 --> 04:03.160
<i>♪ So lose that guy </i>

04:03.360 --> 04:06.820
<i>- ♪ How could you run off</i>
<i>to be somebody's Mrs. ♪</i>

04:07.020 --> 04:10.910
<i>♪ When you could be here </i>
<i> with your Pink Lady sisters? ♪</i>

04:11.110 --> 04:13.210
<i>♪ Yeah, he calls you</i>
<i>an old soul ♪</i>

04:13.410 --> 04:15.220
- <i>♪ But he's just a child </i>
- [crying]

04:15.420 --> 04:17.480
<i>♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh </i>

04:17.680 --> 04:19.650
- <i>all: ♪ Please, please </i>
<i>- ♪ How could you run off </i>

04:19.850 --> 04:22.440
<i>♪ To be somebody's Mrs. </i>

04:22.640 --> 04:26.180
<i>♪ When you could be here </i>
<i> with your Pink Lady sisters? ♪</i>

04:26.380 --> 04:28.530
<i>all: ♪ The apple of eyes </i>

04:28.730 --> 04:30.490
<i>♪ He's not worth your time </i>

04:30.690 --> 04:32.620
<i>♪ So lose that guy </i>

04:32.820 --> 04:36.110
That's enough!

04:36.310 --> 04:37.630
Who the hell
do you think you are?

04:37.830 --> 04:39.370
Your friends.

04:39.570 --> 04:40.980
And because we're your friends,
we're here to tell you

04:41.180 --> 04:43.030
that, honestly,
you're being really stupid.

04:43.230 --> 04:44.280
Stupid?

04:45.800 --> 04:47.680
Wow.

04:47.880 --> 04:51.430
Maybe what's stupid
is playing make believe

04:51.630 --> 04:54.340
in some pink clubhouse while
real-life things are happening.

04:54.540 --> 04:56.910
I know how real things are.

04:57.110 --> 04:58.870
That's why we need you
to put an end to this madness

04:59.070 --> 05:00.090
and help us get Richie back.

05:00.290 --> 05:02.220
Wake up.

05:02.420 --> 05:05.130
Richie isn't coming back.

05:05.330 --> 05:07.400
And I'm getting married.

05:07.600 --> 05:09.100
A true friend would be happy
that there's at least

05:09.290 --> 05:10.620
one good thing
in my life right now.

05:10.820 --> 05:13.010
- But you should finish high
school and go to college.

05:13.210 --> 05:15.320
What are you talking about?

05:15.520 --> 05:17.490
My family can't afford college.

05:19.440 --> 05:20.760
Let's be honest.

05:20.960 --> 05:23.280
I'm gonna get married anyway.

05:23.480 --> 05:26.200
Leo cares about me.

05:26.400 --> 05:27.890
He doesn't think I'm stupid.

05:31.150 --> 05:32.200
Please get out.

05:34.110 --> 05:36.300
Out.

05:36.500 --> 05:38.770
- I--that's not what I meant.

05:40.420 --> 05:43.220
Who wants quesadillas?

05:43.420 --> 05:44.570
[growls]

05:44.770 --> 05:47.130
<i>[lively music]</i>
[tires screeching]

05:47.330 --> 05:48.870
[engine roaring]

05:49.070 --> 05:55.920
<i>♪ </i>

05:59.700 --> 06:00.970
- I don't see
what the big deal is.

06:01.170 --> 06:02.320
- It was a big deal.
- What?

06:02.520 --> 06:03.850
- I can't believe
you did that to me.

06:04.050 --> 06:06.200
- What'd you want me to do?
- You could've just stayed.

06:06.400 --> 06:13.240
<i>♪ </i>

06:15.240 --> 06:18.510
- Sorry I was a jerk
to you the other day.

06:18.710 --> 06:20.080
- I would like to--
- Let's celebrate.

06:20.280 --> 06:21.340
Celebrate what?

06:21.540 --> 06:22.860
- We just had our first fight,
baby.

06:23.060 --> 06:23.940
Oh.

06:25.290 --> 06:27.350
Aw, our first fight.

06:27.550 --> 06:29.910
- Now our love
is stronger than ever.

06:31.600 --> 06:34.010
Yes, darling.

06:34.210 --> 06:35.750
Ugh, I don't think my character
would pour the coffee

06:35.950 --> 06:37.710
because she's mad at him.

06:37.910 --> 06:39.230
I can't pour the coffee.

06:39.430 --> 06:40.710
I'm too depressed.

06:40.910 --> 06:42.010
I'll pour the coffee.

06:42.210 --> 06:43.490
- No, you can't
pour the coffee.

06:43.690 --> 06:45.410
You're eight years old
and you have typhoid.

06:45.610 --> 06:46.370
[school bell rings]

06:46.570 --> 06:47.630
This is a mess.

06:47.830 --> 06:50.200
- [sighs]
We'll figure it out tomorrow.

06:50.400 --> 06:51.420
That was terrible.

06:51.610 --> 06:53.330
Terrible.

06:53.530 --> 06:55.590
Maybe it wasn't so bad.

06:55.790 --> 06:58.160
- What are you doing?
- Lydia...

06:58.360 --> 07:00.120
I like you.

07:00.320 --> 07:02.300
I really like you.

07:02.500 --> 07:04.080
The way Romeo likes Juliet.

07:04.280 --> 07:05.690
The way Gene Kelly
likes Debbie Reynolds

07:05.890 --> 07:09.000
in that stupid movie
I secretly kind of like.

07:09.200 --> 07:12.570
[inhales deeply]

07:12.770 --> 07:15.830
I don't know what it means.

07:16.030 --> 07:17.880
I just know

07:18.080 --> 07:22.400
that being with you
just feels...

07:22.600 --> 07:24.480
right.

07:26.660 --> 07:27.660
No.

07:28.790 --> 07:29.800
One minute you're kissing me,

07:30.000 --> 07:31.410
and the next
you're running away.

07:31.610 --> 07:33.240
I'm not gonna do that again.

07:33.440 --> 07:34.710
Again?

07:37.890 --> 07:39.280
Um...

07:41.670 --> 07:44.600
There was a girl
at summer stock.

07:44.800 --> 07:47.470
<i>♪ </i>

07:47.670 --> 07:49.600
We were friends,
and then we were more.

07:49.800 --> 07:51.300
Every night
we'd meet up behind the cabins

07:51.500 --> 07:55.440
and talk, kiss,

07:55.640 --> 07:59.180
until one night
she just didn't show up

07:59.380 --> 08:03.920
and the next day pretended
like nothing even happened.

08:04.120 --> 08:05.660
And when I tried
to get her to admit it,

08:05.860 --> 08:09.010
she said that I was sick
and a deviant.

08:09.210 --> 08:12.020
- But--
- I...

08:12.220 --> 08:14.980
You're not steady ground,
Cynthia.

08:15.180 --> 08:21.550
<i>♪ </i>

08:21.750 --> 08:23.290
- There has to be something
you could do.

08:23.490 --> 08:25.730
- I'm just as upset as you,
but Olivia has already

08:25.930 --> 08:27.210
submitted
her withdrawal papers,

08:27.410 --> 08:29.640
so technically, she's
not even a student anymore.

08:29.840 --> 08:31.650
- My hands are tied.
- [sighs]

08:31.850 --> 08:33.990
Don't you ever get sick
of having your hands tied?

08:36.290 --> 08:37.700
I'm sorry.

08:37.890 --> 08:39.910
It's just the key
to stopping Olivia

08:40.110 --> 08:42.000
from making the biggest mistake
of her life

08:42.200 --> 08:43.480
is getting Richie back.

08:43.680 --> 08:45.920
- I wish there was a way
I could help you, Jane.

08:46.120 --> 08:47.170
I really do.

08:51.350 --> 08:53.360
- It's all Richie's fault.
Think about it.

08:53.560 --> 08:55.020
He's always getting in trouble.

08:55.220 --> 08:57.280
That's why
his parents shipped him off.

08:57.480 --> 08:58.630
Buddy has never
gotten in trouble.

08:58.830 --> 09:00.020
He is the victim here.

09:00.220 --> 09:02.150
- Look, blondie,
I am under a lot of pressure

09:02.350 --> 09:03.760
to clean up
juvenile delinquency.

09:03.960 --> 09:06.290
Unless every single kid who
was inside the Frosty Palace

09:06.490 --> 09:08.160
that night,
including both of those boys,

09:08.360 --> 09:12.160
can agree on whose fault
it was, they're both expelled.

09:12.360 --> 09:14.110
- Principal Nicholson,
if you just--

09:16.680 --> 09:19.430
<i>[despondent music]</i>

09:19.630 --> 09:22.520
<i>[music brightens]</i>

09:22.720 --> 09:23.700
Can't blame a girl for trying.

09:23.900 --> 09:26.130
Susan.

09:26.330 --> 09:27.650
I actually think
you're on to something.

09:36.270 --> 09:39.100
<i>[inquisitive music]</i>

09:39.300 --> 09:42.020
<i>♪ </i>

09:42.220 --> 09:43.590
- There's no reason
why Buddy and Richie

09:43.790 --> 09:46.110
should both have to go down
for the fight.

09:46.310 --> 09:48.770
All Principal Nicholson needs
is someone to blame

09:48.970 --> 09:50.460
to the news,
to the parents.

09:50.660 --> 09:51.860
Just one of them.

09:52.060 --> 09:54.030
- Richie started it.
- Hey, Buddy swung first!

09:54.230 --> 09:55.860
- Are you kidding me?
- Hey, hey, hey, hey! Cool it!

09:56.060 --> 10:02.860
<i>♪ </i>

10:04.560 --> 10:07.180
- We need to settle this
fair and square.

10:07.380 --> 10:08.310
With a race.

10:08.510 --> 10:10.000
Buddy wins,
we all go

10:10.200 --> 10:11.400
to Nicholson and McGee
together.

10:11.600 --> 10:13.790
We say that the fight
was Richie's fault,

10:13.990 --> 10:15.100
and Buddy stays at Rydell.

10:15.300 --> 10:16.530
But if Buddy loses--

10:16.730 --> 10:17.800
How is this gonna work?

10:17.990 --> 10:18.970
Richie's not even here.

10:19.170 --> 10:20.620
I'm his second.

10:20.820 --> 10:22.440
I'll race for him.

10:26.710 --> 10:28.330
- No offense,
but there's no world

10:28.530 --> 10:29.720
in which you beat
Gil Rizzo at a race.

10:29.920 --> 10:31.030
- The T-Birds drag race
all the time.

10:31.230 --> 10:32.370
It's an unfair advantage.

10:32.570 --> 10:34.160
Wait, why are we huddling?

10:34.360 --> 10:37.210
- 'Cause, um, they're huddling,
so I thought we could too.

10:37.410 --> 10:38.730
- Oh, cool. Okay.
- Okay, I like a good huddle.

10:38.930 --> 10:40.250
I'm hungry.

10:40.450 --> 10:42.120
- Buddy's got
a better, newer car.

10:42.320 --> 10:45.300
The T-Birds' car is a jalopy
with a good paint job.

10:45.500 --> 10:48.000
- Pancakes would be nice.
- Should we get a table?

10:48.200 --> 10:52.610
<i>♪ </i>

10:52.810 --> 10:54.750
- Oh!
- They're done.

10:54.940 --> 10:56.920
All right.

10:57.120 --> 10:57.920
Let's do this.

10:58.120 --> 11:01.490
<i>♪ </i>

11:01.690 --> 11:03.930
May the best man win.

11:04.130 --> 11:05.800
[both gasp]

11:06.000 --> 11:07.670
- I can't wait
to be in high school.

11:07.870 --> 11:09.980
- It's so exciting.
- Shh.

11:10.180 --> 11:11.460
What are you doing here?

11:11.660 --> 11:12.550
You're supposed
to be helping out

11:12.750 --> 11:13.850
at the deli.
It's almost 4:00.

11:14.050 --> 11:15.940
- Don't go
shouting your IQ so loud.

11:16.140 --> 11:18.730
- Frenchy, you can't tell
Mom or Dad about any of this.

11:18.930 --> 11:20.990
Oh, we would never, honest.

11:21.190 --> 11:22.730
We're loyal.

11:22.930 --> 11:24.600
Speaking of which...

11:24.800 --> 11:25.990
Oh, we were thinkin'...

11:26.190 --> 11:28.300
Don't hurt yourself.

11:28.500 --> 11:30.430
- Maybe you might need
a couple more Pink Ladies

11:30.630 --> 11:32.300
for moral support
at this race.

11:32.500 --> 11:34.740
Two, to be exact.

11:34.940 --> 11:37.400
- Please, sis?
We got what it takes!

11:37.600 --> 11:39.530
Style, spirit,

11:39.730 --> 11:42.610
and we're as tough
as they come.

11:45.050 --> 11:47.750
[both laugh]

11:47.950 --> 11:50.280
- No. No way.
- Absolutely not.

11:50.480 --> 11:52.190
- There's
a minimum height requirement.

11:52.390 --> 11:54.850
- Oh, but--
- Come on.

11:55.050 --> 11:56.720
I'll drive you home.

11:56.920 --> 11:58.550
Oh, gee, thanks.

11:58.750 --> 12:00.160
Ew, French.

12:00.360 --> 12:01.810
[sighs dreamily]

12:02.010 --> 12:03.340
- Come on.
- Never gonna happen.

12:03.530 --> 12:07.030
<i>♪ </i>

12:07.230 --> 12:08.300
- It should be
the purple glitter.

12:08.500 --> 12:09.780
- Has to be purple.
- No, red.

12:09.980 --> 12:12.080
- It's so pretty.
- I like red too.

12:12.280 --> 12:13.910
For Rydell?

12:14.110 --> 12:15.960
- The purple seems nice.
- It pops.

12:16.160 --> 12:17.310
- Shouldn't we
be doing something

12:17.510 --> 12:18.830
more functionally useful
to help Buddy

12:19.030 --> 12:20.660
than making a banner?

12:20.860 --> 12:23.440
<i>- ♪ Everybody likes</i>
<i>my Rocket '88 ♪</i>

12:23.640 --> 12:25.100
<i>♪ Baby, we'll ride in style </i>

12:25.300 --> 12:26.140
How's the banner comin'?

12:26.340 --> 12:27.710
I'm trying to make friends

12:27.910 --> 12:30.320
because it's awkward just
being the hovering girlfriend,

12:30.520 --> 12:32.190
but it's like
we're from different planets.

12:32.390 --> 12:34.280
I'm sure you'll all warm up.

12:34.480 --> 12:38.020
[tires screeching]

12:38.220 --> 12:41.940
<i>♪ </i>

12:42.140 --> 12:44.070
So how'd I do?

12:44.270 --> 12:45.810
Not...good.

12:46.010 --> 12:48.120
No time for niceties.

12:48.320 --> 12:50.210
My nana has a better chance
of winning than you

12:50.410 --> 12:51.820
with her gout.

12:52.020 --> 12:52.910
- Yeah, well,
the car feels unsteady

12:53.110 --> 12:55.430
when it gets too fast.

12:55.630 --> 12:58.000
It needs wider tires.

12:58.200 --> 13:00.220
They'll make the car
more aerodynamic

13:00.420 --> 13:01.870
by adding weight low
and increasing grip

13:02.070 --> 13:03.050
and friction
with the ground.

13:03.250 --> 13:06.090
[laughter]
both: Friction.

13:06.290 --> 13:07.400
It's just science.

13:07.600 --> 13:08.880
I think it's genius.

13:09.080 --> 13:11.800
More helpful
than you two knuckleheads.

13:11.990 --> 13:12.970
Thank God I got one friend

13:13.170 --> 13:14.270
who knows
what they're talkin' about.

13:16.360 --> 13:17.540
- You heard the lady.
Let's go, boys!

13:17.740 --> 13:20.720
New tires!
both: Tires.

13:20.920 --> 13:23.460
- Looks like you had a friend
in the group already after all.

13:23.660 --> 13:24.620
Yeah.

13:28.630 --> 13:30.600
- Look, it's not the best
carburetor in the world,

13:30.800 --> 13:31.950
but I could beat
Howdy Doody Aldridge

13:32.150 --> 13:33.430
with my eyes closed.

13:33.620 --> 13:34.430
It'll be fine.

13:34.630 --> 13:35.990
Fine isn't good enough,

13:36.190 --> 13:37.650
not when the stakes
are this high.

13:37.850 --> 13:40.260
This is for Richie.

13:40.460 --> 13:41.830
<i>Hola, ratoncito.</i>

13:42.020 --> 13:44.740
- How's it going?
- [shudders]

13:44.940 --> 13:48.480
Okay, if this is going to work,
I have some ground rules.

13:48.680 --> 13:51.530
No public hand-holding,
hugging, or touching.

13:51.730 --> 13:53.310
- [giggles]
You got it.

13:53.510 --> 13:54.970
No cutesy nicknames.

13:55.170 --> 13:57.140
- I--aye-aye, doll face.

13:57.340 --> 13:59.360
- And absolutely
no finishing each other's...

13:59.560 --> 14:02.410
- Sentences?
- Statements.

14:02.610 --> 14:03.930
If you wanna be with me,

14:04.130 --> 14:06.410
you will have to follow
these rules to the letter.

14:06.610 --> 14:08.240
Okay.

14:08.440 --> 14:09.500
I guess.

14:13.240 --> 14:15.470
- Why are you so mean to him?
Don't you like him?

14:15.670 --> 14:17.210
- Relationships
are complicated.

14:17.410 --> 14:19.820
- You've been together
for a week.

14:20.020 --> 14:20.910
You just wouldn't understand

14:21.110 --> 14:22.860
because
you've never been in one.

14:28.300 --> 14:30.260
All right.

14:30.460 --> 14:32.270
We need a new carb.

14:32.470 --> 14:34.920
For increased speed.

14:35.120 --> 14:37.360
That's--that's
what a carburetor does, right?

14:37.560 --> 14:39.320
- I'm guessing from context.
- Just take this.

14:39.520 --> 14:41.060
- Carburetors aren't
one size fits all.

14:41.260 --> 14:43.280
If we find one that fits,
it could make the car faster,

14:43.480 --> 14:44.410
but it could also be a...

14:44.610 --> 14:46.890
[mimics explosion]

14:47.090 --> 14:49.940
- We have to know we've
tried everything we could.

14:50.140 --> 14:53.420
- Okay, but where are we gonna
find a fancy four-barrel carb?

14:53.620 --> 14:56.380
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

14:56.580 --> 15:03.420
<i>♪ </i>

15:08.690 --> 15:10.870
- No, I didn't know
there was assembly required

15:11.070 --> 15:12.390
for the Hall of Mirrors.

15:12.590 --> 15:17.010
Do I sound like an expert
on carnival carpentry?

15:17.210 --> 15:19.710
Wait, wait, wait.

15:19.900 --> 15:21.230
Yes, Ms. McGee?

15:21.430 --> 15:23.320
- This carnival is likely
to be the death of me.

15:23.520 --> 15:25.280
Any luck
finding me an assistant?

15:25.480 --> 15:26.890
- Assistant?
Oh, yeah!

15:27.090 --> 15:29.150
[chuckles] No.

15:29.350 --> 15:30.930
But you are looking, right?

15:31.130 --> 15:33.150
- Absolutely.
I am on it.

15:33.350 --> 15:34.550
<i>- Okay, sounds like...</i>
- No.

15:34.750 --> 15:35.900
<i>- You have</i>
<i>the Hall of Mirrors covered.</i>

15:36.100 --> 15:36.810
- No, he wasn't talking
about the Hall of Mirrors.

15:37.010 --> 15:38.420
<i>- Thanks, bye.</i>
- Hello?

15:38.620 --> 15:40.680
Hello?

15:40.880 --> 15:42.380
- An assistant
for an assistant.

15:42.580 --> 15:44.380
What's next?
A maid for the janitor?

15:44.580 --> 15:46.330
[chuckles]

15:51.290 --> 15:52.780
That was my apple.

15:52.980 --> 15:55.390
<i>[lively music]</i>

15:55.590 --> 15:58.090
Bingo.

15:58.290 --> 16:03.620
<i>♪ </i>

16:03.820 --> 16:06.100
Doing the job of 15 people.

16:06.300 --> 16:09.320
Then he eats my apple.

16:09.520 --> 16:12.280
- [coughs dramatically]
- [neighs]

16:12.480 --> 16:14.060
What's going on here?

16:14.260 --> 16:16.230
What are you doing
to Principal Nicholson's car?

16:19.760 --> 16:20.940
- It's--it's a long story,

16:21.140 --> 16:24.290
but it's to help
get Olivia back in Rydell.

16:24.490 --> 16:26.950
<i>[light tense music]</i>

16:27.150 --> 16:32.910
<i>♪ </i>

16:33.110 --> 16:34.780
You know,

16:34.980 --> 16:38.220
I must need a new prescription
for my spectacles.

16:38.420 --> 16:41.180
I can't seem
to see a darn thing lately.

16:41.380 --> 16:48.220
<i>♪ </i>

16:52.180 --> 16:54.620
- [laughs]
All right.

16:56.140 --> 16:59.020
<i>[wistful music]</i>

16:59.220 --> 17:00.410
<i>♪ </i>

17:00.610 --> 17:04.770
- How you feelin'
about tomorrow?

17:04.970 --> 17:05.900
I really think
the tires will make--

17:06.100 --> 17:07.760
Hazel, I'm gonna lose.

17:09.590 --> 17:10.860
I can't beat Gil.

17:11.060 --> 17:13.200
[insects chirping]

17:15.900 --> 17:19.610
It's just a shame because...
[sighs]

17:19.810 --> 17:22.960
You know, all the things I've
been so focused on this year--

17:23.160 --> 17:26.140
football,
the election,

17:26.340 --> 17:29.260
making my dad happy,
and Jane...

17:33.440 --> 17:35.060
I lost them all.

17:35.260 --> 17:38.450
- I'm sorry.
- Don't be.

17:38.650 --> 17:39.580
I'm not.

17:42.800 --> 17:45.940
What I was going to say
is that without them,

17:46.140 --> 17:48.460
I was just starting
to see everything clearly

17:48.660 --> 17:49.810
for the first time.

17:50.010 --> 17:53.380
You know,
who I actually am,

17:53.580 --> 17:54.890
what I really want...

17:59.120 --> 18:04.610
And all the things I missed,

18:04.810 --> 18:06.990
even though
they were right in front of me.

18:10.780 --> 18:13.360
Hazel, if I weren't leaving,

18:13.560 --> 18:16.230
I would keep my mouth shut
because Wally's my friend--

18:16.430 --> 18:18.840
It's getting late.

18:19.040 --> 18:21.580
You should, um, get some rest.

18:21.780 --> 18:28.230
<i>♪ </i>

18:30.370 --> 18:32.770
Yeah.

18:32.970 --> 18:39.810
<i>♪ </i>

18:45.600 --> 18:48.170
[inhales deeply]

18:48.370 --> 18:50.310
[sighs]

18:50.510 --> 18:52.700
♪ Brusha, brusha, brusha

18:52.900 --> 18:55.050
♪ Here's the new Ipana

18:55.250 --> 18:58.530
♪ With the brand-new flavor,
it's dandy for your teeth ♪

18:58.730 --> 19:00.060
♪ Brusha, brusha, brusha

19:00.260 --> 19:01.490
- both: ♪ Here's the new Ipana
- [gasps]

19:01.690 --> 19:03.620
- What are you doing?
- Hey.

19:03.820 --> 19:05.930
You sound good.

19:06.130 --> 19:07.020
I knew you wouldn't talk
to the girls,

19:07.220 --> 19:09.800
so I came to tell you,

19:10.000 --> 19:12.290
I'm racing Buddy Aldridge
at the track tomorrow.

19:12.490 --> 19:15.930
And if I win,
Richie comes back.

19:17.460 --> 19:20.340
- Lemme guess.
Jane's idea?

19:20.540 --> 19:22.690
- Sorta.
- [scoffs]

19:22.890 --> 19:24.300
I thought you'd be smarter
than to get wrapped up

19:24.500 --> 19:25.780
in her little crusades.

19:25.980 --> 19:27.740
Thinking she can
make everything fair

19:27.940 --> 19:29.480
with hope and sunshine

19:29.680 --> 19:32.520
when we have all the evidence
that nothing is fair.

19:32.720 --> 19:35.300
It's not gonna work,
and you know it.

19:37.260 --> 19:38.490
- Well, it would mean
an awful lot to me

19:38.690 --> 19:40.220
if you showed up anyway.

19:48.360 --> 19:50.100
Gil, I'm getting married.

19:54.490 --> 19:55.850
- I just thought
you should know

19:56.050 --> 19:58.240
at least someone
hasn't given up on Richie.

19:58.440 --> 20:01.200
<i>[bittersweet music]</i>

20:01.400 --> 20:08.250
<i>♪ </i>

20:16.340 --> 20:17.250
[groans]

20:22.300 --> 20:25.180
<i>[exciting music]</i>

20:25.380 --> 20:32.190
<i>♪ </i>

20:32.390 --> 20:35.840
[indistinct chatter]

20:44.850 --> 20:48.340
- Don't be nervous.
This is yours to win.

20:48.540 --> 20:50.040
- Who invited the hussies
from St. Bernadette's?

20:50.230 --> 20:51.650
[wolf whistles]

20:51.850 --> 20:54.740
- And the kids
from Washington High?

20:54.940 --> 20:57.700
This is becoming a circus.

20:57.890 --> 21:02.270
<i>♪ </i>

21:02.460 --> 21:05.010
- Buddy, take it easy.
- She's never looked better.

21:05.210 --> 21:07.920
- Yeah,
she's looking real good.

21:08.120 --> 21:10.100
[laughs]

21:10.300 --> 21:12.320
- Dude, no, you got this.
- No worries.

21:12.520 --> 21:13.960
- [laughs]
- Stop staring.

21:15.530 --> 21:17.930
- I was gonna lose in front
of, like, four people...

21:18.130 --> 21:20.410
- She's purring
like a kitten, boys.

21:20.610 --> 21:22.420
[groans]
[onlookers gasp]

21:22.620 --> 21:23.810
- Aah!
- The strut slipped.

21:24.010 --> 21:25.380
- Come on.
- [grunts]

21:25.570 --> 21:27.680
[gasps, groans]

21:27.880 --> 21:29.250
[laughs]

21:29.450 --> 21:30.900
Nah, it's fine.

21:31.100 --> 21:33.250
It's fine.
I can still race.

21:33.450 --> 21:35.250
- Can you make a fist?
- Ow.

21:35.450 --> 21:36.950
[panting]

21:37.150 --> 21:39.130
[groans]

21:39.330 --> 21:41.520
[winces]

21:41.720 --> 21:43.130
You can't race like this.

21:43.330 --> 21:44.740
Someone has to step up.

21:44.940 --> 21:46.050
Potato will do it.

21:46.250 --> 21:48.350
Me? I can't drive.

21:48.550 --> 21:49.660
I've been asking you guys
to teach me.

21:49.860 --> 21:50.880
- I guess
you'll have to forfeit.

21:51.080 --> 21:51.910
Huh?

21:53.830 --> 21:55.840
No one's forfeiting.

21:56.040 --> 21:56.880
I'll drive.

21:57.080 --> 21:58.320
[laughter]

21:58.520 --> 22:00.020
- Great idea.
Fine by me.

22:00.220 --> 22:01.240
Jane, I'm not gonna race you.

22:01.440 --> 22:03.410
You flunked driver's ed.

22:03.610 --> 22:05.240
They shouldn't have to forfeit.
Gil got hurt.

22:05.440 --> 22:07.290
We should just call it off.

22:07.490 --> 22:09.240
- But then
you'll both still be expelled.

22:10.760 --> 22:12.860
- [sighs]
- I'll race her.

22:13.060 --> 22:14.690
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:14.880 --> 22:16.210
I flunked too.
That's fair.

22:16.410 --> 22:18.560
- No, it's too dangerous.
Someone could get hurt.

22:18.760 --> 22:20.820
- Hey, I know I flunked,
but I am faster than her.

22:21.020 --> 22:22.250
I could win this.

22:24.900 --> 22:26.570
You said during the election

22:26.770 --> 22:28.690
that you wanted to run
fair and square.

22:30.430 --> 22:32.620
You owe me a fair fight.

22:32.820 --> 22:37.270
<i>♪ </i>

22:37.470 --> 22:38.530
Okay.

22:40.350 --> 22:43.240
[cheers and applause]

22:43.440 --> 22:45.980
<i>[anticipatory music]</i>

22:46.180 --> 22:53.020
<i>♪ </i>

22:56.980 --> 23:00.080
[engine turns over]

23:00.280 --> 23:01.820
[engine roars]

23:02.020 --> 23:04.740
[cheers and applause]

23:04.930 --> 23:11.090
<i>♪ </i>

23:11.290 --> 23:14.270
Get ready.

23:14.470 --> 23:17.620
Get setty.

23:17.820 --> 23:20.140
Go!
[tires squealing]

23:20.340 --> 23:21.190
[cheers and applause]

23:21.390 --> 23:23.490
- Come on!
- Susan!

23:23.690 --> 23:25.020
- Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!
[tires screech]

23:25.220 --> 23:26.410
Ooh, sorry!

23:26.610 --> 23:28.110
[tires screeching]

23:28.310 --> 23:30.240
- Susan!
- Which one's reverse?

23:30.440 --> 23:31.460
- What are you doing?
- Come on!

23:31.660 --> 23:33.680
- Release the clutch!
- What's the clutch?

23:33.880 --> 23:36.980
- It's the pedal on the left!
- Wait!

23:37.180 --> 23:39.030
- Really?
- I'm trying.

23:39.230 --> 23:41.340
[grunts]

23:41.540 --> 23:44.430
[tires squealing]
[yells]

23:44.630 --> 23:47.080
- Go!
- Yes!

23:47.280 --> 23:48.910
<i>[John Travolta's</i>
<i>"Greased Lightnin'"]</i>

23:49.110 --> 23:51.300
- Whoo!
- Come on, Jane!

23:51.500 --> 23:56.700
<i>♪ </i>

23:56.900 --> 23:57.700
Go, Jane, go!

23:57.900 --> 24:02.580
<i>♪ </i>

24:02.780 --> 24:03.920
- Come on!
Come on! Come on!

24:04.120 --> 24:09.760
<i>♪ </i>

24:09.960 --> 24:11.620
- You gotta go faster
than that!

24:13.360 --> 24:14.320
- Get it, Jane!
- You got it! You got it!

24:16.100 --> 24:17.500
- I thought those tires were
supposed to make a difference.

24:17.700 --> 24:18.810
- What's the deal?
- Jane's gonna win.

24:19.010 --> 24:21.860
[screams]

24:22.060 --> 24:24.290
[indistinct shouting]

24:24.490 --> 24:25.730
Go faster!

24:25.930 --> 24:29.650
<i>♪ </i>

24:29.850 --> 24:32.820
[car sputtering]

24:33.020 --> 24:34.730
- She's pushing it too hard!
- You got it! You got it!

24:36.560 --> 24:40.180
Final lap!

24:40.380 --> 24:41.530
- Come on!
What is she doing?

24:41.730 --> 24:44.490
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

24:44.690 --> 24:45.840
<i>♪ </i>

24:46.040 --> 24:47.450
Ha ha! Ha ha!

24:47.650 --> 24:49.670
- You can do this, Susan!
- Keep going! Floor it!

24:49.870 --> 24:51.960
- Come on, Jane!
Don't let up now!

24:54.180 --> 24:55.760
- Yes!
- Come on, Susan!

24:55.960 --> 24:59.150
[shouting]

24:59.350 --> 25:01.680
- She's smokin' her!
- You got this, Susan!

25:01.880 --> 25:04.640
<i>♪ </i>

25:04.840 --> 25:05.640
[car sputtering]

25:05.840 --> 25:07.900
[engine roars]

25:08.100 --> 25:08.980
They're neck and neck!

25:14.290 --> 25:15.510
Keep it steady, Jane.

25:18.600 --> 25:19.780
- Come on.
Come on. Come on.

25:19.980 --> 25:23.050
<i>[music crescendos]</i>

25:23.250 --> 25:25.790
<i>♪ </i>

25:25.990 --> 25:27.490
[tires hissing]

25:27.690 --> 25:29.230
- No!
- No!

25:29.430 --> 25:32.010
Ha ha! Ha ha ha!

25:32.210 --> 25:34.670
Whoo!

25:34.870 --> 25:36.150
[cheers and applause]

25:36.350 --> 25:37.980
Whoo-hoo!

25:38.170 --> 25:39.620
Whoo!

25:41.750 --> 25:44.070
[sighs]

25:44.270 --> 25:47.510
[cheers and applause]

25:47.710 --> 25:49.990
<i>[melancholic music]</i>

25:50.190 --> 25:56.990
<i>♪ </i>

26:12.610 --> 26:15.480
[cheers and applause]

26:17.960 --> 26:19.400
Ugh! What did I say?

26:22.660 --> 26:23.980
What? I warned him.

26:24.180 --> 26:25.680
He's being impossible.

26:25.870 --> 26:28.070
- You know
who's impossible, Nancy?

26:28.270 --> 26:29.450
You.

26:32.720 --> 26:35.340
- Susan, that was the most!
both: To say the least!

26:35.540 --> 26:36.810
I know.

26:41.460 --> 26:42.690
[sighs]

26:42.890 --> 26:45.700
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

26:45.890 --> 26:51.570
<i>♪ </i>

26:51.770 --> 26:54.570
Well, fair is fair.

26:54.770 --> 26:55.920
Hey! [laughs]

26:56.120 --> 26:59.100
Come on.
Let's celebrate!

26:59.300 --> 27:01.840
<i>[bittersweet music]</i>

27:02.040 --> 27:03.410
- Whoo-hoo!

27:03.610 --> 27:05.580
[laughs]

27:05.780 --> 27:07.110
I can't believe it.
Buddy can stay!

27:07.310 --> 27:08.760
We get our friend back!

27:08.960 --> 27:11.330
Yeah.

27:11.530 --> 27:13.070
- All right!
[cheering]

27:13.270 --> 27:17.150
- all: Susan! Susan! Susan!
- Oh, my God.

27:19.630 --> 27:21.250
[knocks at door]

27:21.450 --> 27:22.600
[door opens]

27:22.800 --> 27:25.170
Hi.

27:25.370 --> 27:27.170
Is Papa Zdunowski home?

27:27.370 --> 27:30.570
- He's taking a look
at Gil's car out in the shop.

27:30.770 --> 27:32.740
Great.

27:32.940 --> 27:35.090
'Cause I brought
a peace offering.

27:35.290 --> 27:36.620
I don't really want company.

27:36.820 --> 27:38.440
- Well, then you should
lock your doors.

27:38.640 --> 27:40.010
[sighs]

27:40.210 --> 27:43.620
Look, this doesn't have
to be a whole thing, okay?

27:43.820 --> 27:46.800
I just don't like
how you talk to Potato.

27:47.000 --> 27:47.930
He's a good guy.

27:48.130 --> 27:49.010
[imitates buzzer]

27:50.840 --> 27:53.810
I was a jerk to Potato,
and you were right about that.

27:54.010 --> 27:57.030
But...
[sighs]

27:57.230 --> 28:00.550
Something else is up with you.

28:00.750 --> 28:02.510
Mm, I know

28:02.710 --> 28:04.640
you didn't wanna talk
after you bailed on the play,

28:04.840 --> 28:07.690
but you've been
acting strange all over.

28:07.890 --> 28:10.340
Did something happen?

28:10.540 --> 28:12.030
Is it Shy Guy?

28:15.950 --> 28:17.340
Is your dad okay?

28:20.740 --> 28:21.960
Did you hear from your mom?

28:27.270 --> 28:28.790
You can tell me anything.

28:34.360 --> 28:36.320
- You don't wanna talk about it?
- [sniffles]

28:42.150 --> 28:44.030
[sighs]

28:44.230 --> 28:46.420
- [sobbing]
- You can't talk about it?

28:47.940 --> 28:49.330
Okay.

28:58.380 --> 29:01.300
[rummaging]

29:04.130 --> 29:05.780
Can you write it down?

29:12.620 --> 29:15.230
[sniffles, sighs]

29:23.190 --> 29:26.590
[scribbling]

29:54.350 --> 29:55.440
[clears throat]

30:23.690 --> 30:25.960
[laughs]

30:26.160 --> 30:28.920
<i>[disconsolate music]</i>

30:29.120 --> 30:34.450
<i>♪ </i>

30:34.640 --> 30:37.450
[sobbing]

30:37.650 --> 30:44.490
<i>♪ </i>

30:55.850 --> 30:58.690
<i>[vocalizing]</i>

30:58.890 --> 31:02.780
<i>♪ </i>

31:02.980 --> 31:05.820
[sobbing]

31:06.020 --> 31:12.820
<i>♪ </i>

31:18.870 --> 31:20.870
[birds chirping]

31:24.230 --> 31:26.800
[soft thump]

31:27.000 --> 31:28.930
Richie?

31:31.280 --> 31:33.240
Hazel?

31:33.440 --> 31:34.770
- I--I thought you were--
- Sorry.

31:34.970 --> 31:36.770
[softly]
Um, I know it's early,

31:36.970 --> 31:38.380
but I desperately need
to speak to you.

31:38.580 --> 31:40.470
And I didn't wanna wake
the rest of your family,

31:40.670 --> 31:42.730
- hence the window.
- Okay. What's wrong?

31:42.930 --> 31:45.600
- Um, everything--nothing.

31:45.800 --> 31:48.560
I'm having boy problems,
and I haven't slept all night.

31:48.760 --> 31:51.040
And sleep deprivation causes
poor brain function, Jane,

31:51.240 --> 31:52.960
- and we--
- Hazel.

31:53.160 --> 31:55.310
If I can be totally honest,

31:55.510 --> 32:00.440
I'm not in a really good place
to talk about boy problems.

32:01.960 --> 32:03.190
I'm such an idiot.

32:03.390 --> 32:05.010
Um, I'm sorry.

32:05.210 --> 32:07.410
Um, I'll just climb back out.

32:07.610 --> 32:08.490
- Um--
- Wait.

32:14.540 --> 32:17.840
They say
misery loves company, right?

32:20.370 --> 32:21.460
Oh, yes.

32:24.290 --> 32:27.780
Okay, I think two boys like me,
which is why I came to you,

32:27.980 --> 32:29.040
because you're
the only person I know

32:29.240 --> 32:30.520
who has experience
in this arena.

32:30.720 --> 32:32.260
And it's tricky
because I'm dating Wally,

32:32.460 --> 32:33.740
and he's so wonderful,

32:33.940 --> 32:35.610
but then there's Buddy,
who seems to like me too,

32:35.810 --> 32:38.260
which is nice
because I liked him so much

32:38.460 --> 32:39.570
and--this is weird, right?

32:39.770 --> 32:41.140
- Since you used to go with him?
- Mm-hmm.

32:41.340 --> 32:42.490
- Trust me, the awkwardness
of this conversation

32:42.690 --> 32:43.970
is not lost on me.

32:44.170 --> 32:46.320
Anyhoo, my logical brain
has always gotten me through

32:46.520 --> 32:49.100
complicated situations before,
but it's failing me now,

32:49.300 --> 32:52.490
and can't you
just tell me what to do?

32:54.010 --> 32:57.410
Well, that's a lot.

32:57.610 --> 32:59.110
Yeah.

32:59.310 --> 33:02.250
- And I'm not sure if I can
even offer any advice here.

33:02.440 --> 33:04.810
The last time
I had a two-boy problem,

33:05.010 --> 33:08.080
I ruined both their lives.

33:08.280 --> 33:10.820
Right, that's true.

33:11.020 --> 33:12.210
Shoot.

33:12.410 --> 33:14.000
And I'm sorry to tell you,

33:14.200 --> 33:16.560
but I don't think logic
is all that helpful

33:16.760 --> 33:18.260
in matters of the heart.

33:18.460 --> 33:19.350
[whines]

33:19.550 --> 33:22.610
<i>[mellow music]</i>

33:22.810 --> 33:25.750
You know what's strange?

33:25.950 --> 33:30.530
I feel better
just having told someone.

33:30.730 --> 33:32.880
I don't really have anyone else
I can talk to like this

33:33.080 --> 33:36.890
besides Buddy and Wally,
and, well...

33:37.090 --> 33:38.790
- you know.
- [chuckles]

33:41.100 --> 33:44.420
Hey, you hungry?

33:44.620 --> 33:47.330
<i>[Rosco Gordon's "Booted"]</i>

33:47.530 --> 33:48.810
<i>♪ </i>

33:49.010 --> 33:52.470
Keep it coming, pal.

33:52.670 --> 33:54.080
- Since when
do you drink coffee?

33:54.280 --> 33:56.250
- Since when
do you talk so loud?

33:58.600 --> 34:00.000
So this is it, huh?

34:00.200 --> 34:02.000
My friendship
with Olivia is officially over?

34:02.200 --> 34:04.000
- Why can't you be friends
with Olivia anymore?

34:04.200 --> 34:05.790
'Cause she's getting married.

34:05.990 --> 34:06.790
Oh.

34:06.990 --> 34:09.130
[slurps]

34:12.090 --> 34:15.800
- Sorry, so why can't you
be friends anymore?

34:16.000 --> 34:17.490
- Okay, because...
- Because...

34:17.690 --> 34:18.530
Um...

34:23.230 --> 34:27.630
- Uh, that is
a really good question.

34:27.830 --> 34:29.160
[silverware clatters]
We have to get to Olivia.

34:29.360 --> 34:30.380
I know what we have
to say to her.

34:30.580 --> 34:31.940
- But the wedding
is starting right now.

34:32.140 --> 34:33.950
- Okay.
How far is the church?

34:34.150 --> 34:35.030
All the way across town.

34:35.230 --> 34:36.600
- About a 45-minute walk.

34:36.800 --> 34:38.300
We need a car.
What about Gil's?

34:38.500 --> 34:39.520
Still in the shop.

34:39.720 --> 34:41.640
- And my parents
are on a grocery run.

34:43.860 --> 34:45.520
[indistinct chatter]

34:45.720 --> 34:47.000
Oh!

34:47.200 --> 34:48.700
Good morning, ladies.

34:48.900 --> 34:52.490
It's fortuitous
I ran into you all.

34:52.690 --> 34:54.360
There's something I wanna say.

34:54.560 --> 34:57.190
You Pink Ladies have been
a real thorn in my side

34:57.390 --> 35:00.280
this year,
but despite our conflicts,

35:00.480 --> 35:03.890
I have to admit...

35:04.090 --> 35:05.590
you've inspired me.

35:05.790 --> 35:06.850
Because of you, I've--

35:07.050 --> 35:09.240
I've learned
to stand up for myself,

35:09.440 --> 35:13.290
to work around
unfair policies and prac--

35:13.490 --> 35:14.900
- No!
- It's for Olivia!

35:15.100 --> 35:16.290
- We'll bring it back!
- You--

35:16.490 --> 35:17.820
Thanks a mill, Miss McGee.

35:18.010 --> 35:20.120
[groans]

35:20.320 --> 35:21.560
Come back here, girls!

35:21.760 --> 35:22.860
Get out of my--
get out of my--

35:23.060 --> 35:24.690
go get someone's check!

35:24.890 --> 35:27.910
[girls cheering]

35:28.110 --> 35:29.340
Hey!

35:33.470 --> 35:35.620
You could've just asked
for a ride!

35:35.820 --> 35:38.440
[playing Felix Mendelssohn's
"Wedding March"]

35:38.640 --> 35:45.490
♪

36:22.480 --> 36:24.970
She'll be okay.

36:25.170 --> 36:26.620
He cares for her.

36:26.820 --> 36:28.100
[speaks Spanish]

36:28.300 --> 36:31.450
- In the name of the Father,
the Son,

36:31.650 --> 36:32.930
and the Holy--

36:33.130 --> 36:35.550
- [door opens]
- Wait!

36:35.740 --> 36:38.680
[panting]
[sneakers squeaking]

36:38.880 --> 36:40.150
Peace be with you.

36:43.330 --> 36:46.640
[indistinct whispering]

36:46.840 --> 36:48.170
- Sorry to interrupt.
Can we talk?

36:48.370 --> 36:49.730
We're a little busy.

36:49.930 --> 36:50.910
- [whispers]
Please just go.

36:51.110 --> 36:52.430
- We can't.
- We're your friends.

36:52.630 --> 36:53.650
- And friends show up
for each other

36:53.850 --> 36:55.560
no matter
what dingbats they're marrying.

37:00.470 --> 37:03.880
If I didn't have all of you,

37:04.080 --> 37:06.840
especially you,

37:07.040 --> 37:10.620
bearing witness to everything
that happened this year

37:10.820 --> 37:15.890
and reminding me that
no matter what choices I made

37:16.090 --> 37:19.940
or what the world thought of me

37:20.140 --> 37:24.900
that I was worth something,

37:25.100 --> 37:27.210
I wouldn't have
survived any of it.

37:27.410 --> 37:31.300
<i>♪ </i>

37:31.500 --> 37:36.080
So if you want
to get out of here,

37:36.280 --> 37:39.910
we stole McGee's car
and it is running outside.

37:40.110 --> 37:45.620
But if you really want
to get married,

37:45.810 --> 37:49.270
then you have three bridesmaids
ready to go.

37:49.470 --> 37:52.230
<i>♪ </i>

37:52.430 --> 37:55.800
- I can drape three dresses
out of these in 15 minutes.

37:56.000 --> 37:58.580
<i>♪ </i>

37:58.780 --> 38:00.800
- I'm okay with them staying
if you are.

38:07.540 --> 38:10.330
- When I lost Richie, I thought
I was losing everything.

38:12.420 --> 38:15.040
So I wanted
to hold on to someone

38:15.240 --> 38:17.290
I thought
that I could count on.

38:22.820 --> 38:24.860
But now, I realize that...

38:27.390 --> 38:29.400
I have three,

38:29.600 --> 38:31.880
maybe four,

38:32.080 --> 38:35.000
someones who will never
leave my side no matter what.

38:46.100 --> 38:48.320
This isn't right,
and we both know it.

38:52.930 --> 38:54.680
Maybe you should call Barb.

38:56.590 --> 38:57.940
She seemed nice.

39:01.420 --> 39:04.390
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

39:04.590 --> 39:06.300
[laughter]

39:06.500 --> 39:09.050
- Come on! Come on!
- Yes!

39:09.250 --> 39:13.960
<i>♪ </i>

39:14.160 --> 39:16.310
Wait!

39:16.510 --> 39:20.230
<i>♪ </i>

39:20.430 --> 39:21.230
[all gasp]

39:21.430 --> 39:23.320
She's a child.

39:23.520 --> 39:25.670
<i>♪ </i>

39:25.870 --> 39:27.150
- Yes!
[laughter]

39:27.350 --> 39:28.500
Come on! Come on!
Come on! Come on!

39:28.700 --> 39:35.550
<i>♪ </i>

39:35.750 --> 39:38.510
[indistinct chatter]

39:38.710 --> 39:43.340
<i>♪ </i>

39:43.540 --> 39:46.210
[bell dings]
[cheers and applause]

39:46.410 --> 39:53.260
<i>♪ </i>

39:56.170 --> 39:57.390
Go get 'em, champ.

40:00.220 --> 40:01.580
Go get 'em.

40:01.780 --> 40:03.220
Okay. Okay, jeez.

