- I really want to believe you,
but how can I be sure

43:02.960 --> 43:05.540
that you won't just act
like this never happened?

43:05.740 --> 43:07.060
It's a little late for that.

43:12.320 --> 43:14.240
I told Nancy everything.

43:16.370 --> 43:18.940
And I forget nothing.

43:20.770 --> 43:23.160
There's no going back now.

43:25.770 --> 43:27.260
- I don't have all day,
you know?

43:27.460 --> 43:34.300
<i>♪ </i>

43:45.880 --> 43:48.750
[indistinct chatter]

43:51.580 --> 43:52.670
- Oh!
- Aw, man!

43:57.800 --> 44:01.080
I want to apologize again.

44:01.280 --> 44:02.770
The thing is,

44:02.970 --> 44:06.560
I'm not normal
and I don't want to be.

44:06.760 --> 44:09.090
In life or love.

44:09.280 --> 44:10.650
I get bored easily,

44:10.850 --> 44:14.220
and maybe that means that
even though I like you a lot,

44:14.420 --> 44:15.830
- we shouldn't--
- Okay, that's it!

44:16.030 --> 44:17.400
- Whoa!
- My corn!

44:17.600 --> 44:19.230
You're fake and a phony!

44:19.430 --> 44:20.840
I wish
I never laid eyes on you!

44:21.040 --> 44:22.930
Nancy Nakagawa,
we are through!

44:23.120 --> 44:29.920
<i>♪ </i>

44:31.930 --> 44:33.680
Oh!

44:33.870 --> 44:35.630
- [crowd gasps]
- [whistles]

44:35.830 --> 44:37.720
[applause]

44:37.920 --> 44:38.900
What are you doing?

44:39.100 --> 44:40.770
- I'm keeping things
interesting.

44:40.970 --> 44:46.910
<i>♪ </i>

44:47.110 --> 44:49.340
[gasps and laughter]

44:49.540 --> 44:56.380
<i>♪ </i>

44:57.650 --> 44:59.000
Wait.

44:59.200 --> 45:01.080
Come back.

45:06.000 --> 45:08.570
- Sorry we...
- Robbed me?

45:11.270 --> 45:13.370
Assuming this carnival
isn't your honeymoon,

45:13.570 --> 45:15.240
does this mean you're back,
Miss Valdovinos?

45:15.440 --> 45:18.280
- Yes, Miss McGee.
I'm back.

45:18.480 --> 45:20.720
- Sorry I'm late.
Car's in the shop.

45:20.920 --> 45:21.980
Darndest thing.

45:22.180 --> 45:24.730
Hey, the carnival looks great!

45:24.930 --> 45:26.860
And you did it just fine
all on your own, Miss McGee.

45:27.060 --> 45:29.120
[chuckles]

45:29.320 --> 45:30.690
I managed,

45:30.890 --> 45:32.520
but if I don't
have an assistant

45:32.720 --> 45:34.650
the day I come back
from winter break,

45:34.850 --> 45:36.040
I'll not only quit,

45:36.240 --> 45:37.870
I'll write
a very informative letter

45:38.070 --> 45:39.570
to Superintendent Fletcher

45:39.770 --> 45:42.960
telling him exactly how much
work you do around here!

45:43.160 --> 45:44.350
Got it?

45:46.170 --> 45:47.130
Hmm!

45:50.130 --> 45:51.840
There you are.

45:52.040 --> 45:54.450
Jane, isn't there something
you've just been, mm ,

45:54.650 --> 45:58.850
dying to tell
Principal Nicholson?

45:59.050 --> 46:02.810
- The fight at the Frosty
Palace was Richie's fault.

46:03.010 --> 46:06.250
We all saw it,
and we all agree.

46:06.450 --> 46:07.760
Buddy should stay at Rydell.

46:10.550 --> 46:11.900
Nope, too late.

46:12.100 --> 46:13.510
Buddy Aldridge
gave me a call this morning

46:13.710 --> 46:14.730
and confessed to everything.

46:14.930 --> 46:16.870
Richie Valdovinos
is free to come back.

46:17.060 --> 46:17.950
Really?

46:18.150 --> 46:19.650
- I'm sorry.
He what?

46:19.850 --> 46:21.910
- [laughter]
- He's back!

46:22.110 --> 46:23.740
[laughter]

46:23.940 --> 46:28.140
- Thank you for being you
and...

46:28.340 --> 46:32.230
for not giving up
on Richie or me.

46:32.430 --> 46:33.490
Well, I couldn't have done it

46:33.690 --> 46:35.620
without the girl
who taught me to be bold.

46:35.820 --> 46:37.530
[laughter]

46:40.530 --> 46:43.370
- Ooh, better luck next time,
spaghetti arms.

46:43.570 --> 46:45.280
[laughs]

46:45.480 --> 46:47.580
Oh, that's not gonna do it. No.

46:48.840 --> 46:50.110
That's how you do that.

46:54.240 --> 46:57.340
<i>[gentle music]</i>

46:57.540 --> 47:04.380
<i>♪ </i>

47:11.820 --> 47:14.710
[giggling]

47:14.910 --> 47:21.270
<i>♪ </i>

47:24.790 --> 47:27.540
- Why the hell
would you do that, Buddy?

47:27.740 --> 47:29.940
Are you trying
to make things worse for me?

47:30.140 --> 47:32.640
I got tired

47:32.840 --> 47:34.200
of winning by default.

47:34.400 --> 47:35.860
- Well, big shot,
I hope you like Connecticut,

47:36.060 --> 47:38.690
because first thing tomorrow
morning, you're on a bus.

47:38.890 --> 47:40.820
- No, I'm staying here.
- Not under my roof you're not.

47:41.020 --> 47:41.990
Fine.

47:42.190 --> 47:43.560
- What do you think
you're gonna do?

47:43.760 --> 47:46.990
You're 16 and you just
got kicked out of school!

47:48.690 --> 47:50.920
I don't know.

47:51.120 --> 47:52.310
I'll figure it out.

47:52.510 --> 47:59.350
<i>♪ </i>

48:08.750 --> 48:10.630
- Oh, boy.
Gonna be a dry day.

48:10.830 --> 48:12.020
- Yep.
- Give me that.

48:12.220 --> 48:13.980
- I can make toast for someone,
if you'd like.

48:14.180 --> 48:15.640
No, no, no, wait--
<i>[buzzer buzzes]</i>

48:15.840 --> 48:17.630
[laughter]

48:20.280 --> 48:23.070
[coughs]
Oh, I drank so much of it.

48:25.330 --> 48:28.560
- It was pretty incredible how
you saved the day today, Hazel.

48:28.760 --> 48:32.570
You know, I might not have an
answer to your two-boy problem,

48:32.770 --> 48:36.400
but how about a four-girl
solution to everything else?

48:36.600 --> 48:37.790
- What?
- See?

48:37.990 --> 48:39.140
We've got a problem of our own.

48:39.340 --> 48:41.790
We've got
one unshakable optimist.

48:41.990 --> 48:44.100
- Hi.
- One cool cynic.

48:44.300 --> 48:46.230
One hilarious jokester.

48:46.430 --> 48:49.150
And one mad genius.

48:49.350 --> 48:51.020
But here's the thing:

48:51.220 --> 48:53.200
we're all insane.

48:53.390 --> 48:54.810
- Yeah.
- We are.

48:55.010 --> 48:58.070
We could use a logical one,
the kind of logical one

48:58.270 --> 49:01.420
who uses her powers
to steal a car for a friend?

49:01.620 --> 49:05.940
[mimics drum roll]

49:07.640 --> 49:09.690
- Oh, wow.
- What? I always carry a spare.

49:09.890 --> 49:12.210
[laughter]

49:12.410 --> 49:14.690
- It's yours,
if you want it.

49:14.890 --> 49:16.610
Well,
after you take the pledge.

49:16.810 --> 49:18.790
- We don't have a pledge.
- Not yet.

49:18.990 --> 49:21.140
- [clears throat]
- You don't need to--oh!

49:21.340 --> 49:24.660
The Pink Lady pledge is:

49:24.860 --> 49:27.270
To act cool.

49:27.470 --> 49:29.270
To look cool.

49:29.470 --> 49:32.670
And to be cool.

49:32.870 --> 49:34.890
Till death do us part,

49:35.090 --> 49:37.410
think pink.

49:37.610 --> 49:39.420
- There's just one,
tiny problem.

49:39.610 --> 49:43.200
I'm not cool.

